---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Replicate docs"
  description="Run Thumbrella through Replicate when that matches your deployment model."
>
  <Section
    eyebrow="replicate"
    title="Use Thumbrella from Replicate"
    lede="Choose this path when your team already distributes workloads through Replicate and wants Thumbrella available in the same place."
  >
    <ol>
      <li>Use your Replicate account and standard workflow.</li>
      <li>Run the published Thumbrella model with a media input.</li>
      <li>Account for Replicate usage fees in your deployment model.</li>
    </ol>
    <pre><code>replicate run peter/thumbrella input=https://example.com/media.mp4</code></pre>
    <p>
      Thumbrella does not add an extra charge in this mode, but Replicate billing still applies.
      This is the right option when marketplace distribution and familiar provisioning matter more
      than running the binary directly.
    </p>
  </Section>
</MainLayout>